metadata.name: "Fake News"
metadata.description:
"Fake News" is a powerful and timely photograph that captures a universal truth about the media. Taken at Slab City in California, this image features a man lost in thought as he stares at screens displaying the words "Fake News." The composition and subject matter of the photo convey a sense of urgency and resonance, making it a timeless depiction of the fake news that surrounds us on a daily basis.

This photograph speaks volumes and is sure to resonate with viewers from all walks of life. Whether you're in California or on the other side of the world, the message of "Fake News" is one that we can all relate to.
